definition.value: This is an AE which is defined as an unpleasant, abnormal sense of touch.
This is an AE which occurs when one or more of the body's senses experiences over-stimulation from the environment.
This is an AE which is an abnormal sensation of the  mucosal skin (tingling, pricking, chilling, burning, numbness) with no apparent physical cause.
This is an AE which is numbness or pain in the outer thigh not caused by injury to the thigh, but by injury to a nerve that extends from the spinal column to the thigh.
This is an AE which is a detectable change in the physical or chemical structure of an organism's internal or external environment and has slow response to stimuli.
This is an AE which is a detectable change in the physical or chemical structure of an organism's internal or external environment and is hyporesponsive to stimuli.
This is an AE which is a detectable change in the physical or chemical structure of an organism's internal or external environment and is hyperresponsive to stimuli.
This is an AE which refers the ability of an organism or organ to respond to external stimuli such as weather change.
This is an AE which is a state of low mood and aversion to activity.
This is an AE which is a condition in which a person with a disability is cognitively unaware of having it due to an underlying physical condition.
This is an AE which is an instinct or thought process that is believed to be heavily influenced by anxiety or fear, often to the point of delusion and irrationality.
This is an AE which is a set of delusional conditions in which the affected persons believe they are being persecuted, despite a lack of evidence.
This is an AE which is transitory pain that comes on suddenly and is not alleviated by the patient's regular pain management.
This is an AE which is suggested to be similar to classic migraines, with cortical spreading depression leading to aura formation but without an associated headache.
This is an AE which is memory-based delusion or confabulation, or an inability to distinguish between real and fantasy memories.

This is an AE which is a neurodevelopmental disorder characterized by significant difficulties in social interaction and nonverbal communication, along with restricted and repetitive patterns of behavior and interests.
This is an AE which is a borrowed French word expressing the feeling that one has lived through the present situation before.
This is an AE which is a memory disorder characterized by sudden retrograde episodic memory loss, said to occur for a period of time ranging from hours to years to decades.
This is an AE which is the most common type of primary headache.
This is an AE which is an extreme or irrational fear or phobia of heights, especially when one is not particularly high up.
This is an AE which is a mental and behavioral disorder, specifically an anxiety disorder characterized by reoccurring unexpected panic attacks.
This is an AE which is a mixed  perception in the absence of an external stimulus that has the qualities of a real perception.
This is an AE which is human vocal communication using language and is disorganised.
This is an AE which is a cortical development malformation that is commonly associated with refractory epilepsy.
This is an AE which is neurological disorders caused by clumps of gray matter (nodules of neurons) located in the wrong part of the brain.
This is an AE which refers to an inflammation of the pituitary gland and is rare .
This is an AE which is characterized by persistent antisocial behavior, impaired empathy and remorse, and bold, disinhibited, and egotistical traits.

This is an AE which is damage to a person's mind as a result of one or more events that cause overwhelming amounts of stress that exceed the person's ability to cope or integrate the emotions involved, eventually leading to serious, long-term negative consequences.
This is an AE which is a neurological disorder whose key defining characteristic is a temporary but almost total disruption of short-term memory with a range of problems accessing older memories.
This is an AE which is the fear of confined spaces.
This is an AE which is a key component in all modern etiological models of insomnia disorder.

This is an AE which refers to the property of a vaccine of being able to produce common, "expected" adverse reactions, especially excessive immunological responses and associated signs and symptoms, including fever and sore arm at the injection site.
This is an AE which is a fear of being on an airplane, or other flying vehicle, such as a helicopter, while in flight.
This is an AE which is the specific phobia of isolation; a morbid fear of being egotistical, or a dread of being alone or isolated.
This is an AE which is the experience of the transitional state from wakefulness to sleep: the hypnagogic state of consciousness, during the onset of sleep.
This is an AE which is a common disabling condition following brain damage to the right hemisphere.
This is an AE which is a distortion of the senses, which can reveal how the human brain normally organizes and interprets sensory stimulation.
This is an AE which refers a memory is suddenly and unexpectedly revisited.

This is an AE which is a cognitive disorder of face perception in which the ability to recognize familiar faces, including one's own face (self-recognition), is impaired, while other aspects of visual processing (e.g., object discrimination) and intellectual functioning (e.g., decision-making) remain intact.
This is an AE which is an alteration in the perception of the external world, causing sufferers to perceive it as unreal, distant, distorted or falsified.
This is an AE which is an intrinsic feature of a living matter.
This is an AE which is a hypnopompic perception in the absence of an external stimulus that has the qualities of a real perception.
This is an AE which is a fixed belief that is not amenable to change in light of conflicting evidence.
This is an AE which is a mental and behavioral disorder classified as a Dissociative disorder and a Dissociative [conversion] disorder.
This is an AE which occurs due to a difference between actual and expected motion.
This is an AE which is an awakening occurring earlier (more than 30 minutes) than desired with an inability to go back to sleep, and before total sleep time reaches 6.5 hours.
This is an AE which is the process of diverting the attention of an individual or group from a desired area of focus and thereby blocking or diminishing the reception of desired information.

This is an AE which is a subtype of delusion that occur in patients suffering from a wide range of psychiatric diseases, including two-thirds of patients in manic state of bipolar disorder, half of those with schizophrenia, patients with the grandiose subtype of delusional disorder, and a substantial portion of those with substance abuse disorders.

This is an AE which is a mental and behavioral disorder,specifically an anxiety disorder characterized by symptoms of anxiety in situations where the person perceives their environment to be unsafe with no easy way to escape.

This is an AE which is an emotional and occasionally psychological state experienced when an individual is left without anything in particular to do, is not interested in their surroundings, or feels that a day or period is dull or tedious.
